mindmap
  root((HAIC Type 1 Reinsertion Paper))
    Background
      Type Classification (Deschamps 2010)
        Type I: endhole + CHA/PHA free-floating
        Type II: sidehole + GDA fixed
        Type III: sidehole + intrahepatic branch
        Type IV: sidehole via SMA
      Historical
        Arai 1982 first Type I-like
        Tanaka 2003 fixed-tip developed
        Deschamps 2010 Type I 50% migration
        Meyblum 2025 Type I 0% in reinsertion
    Our Hypothesis
      Type 2 dysfunction reinsertion as Type 1
      Mild curve, no loop
      Free-floating CHA/PHA tip
      No new fixation
      6 cases, less migration
    Novelty STRONG GAP
      Meyblum 0 of 45 Type I at reinsertion
      Iguchi only 1 of 18 CHA tip
      Deschamps Type I primary only
      Reinsertion specific Type I unstudied
    Mechanism Hypotheses
      Plausible (4)
        H1 Vascular remodeling
          Old hose vs new hose
          Reinsertion specific
        H2 Reduced patient activity
          Advanced cancer ECOG 1-2
          Less mechanical stress
        HA Wall friction at curve apex
          Bow shape pressing wall
        HC Less torsional stress (Hu 2019)
          Twisted laundry vs folded paper
      Weakened (5)
        Coil mass effect (no imaging proof)
        Skeletonization splinting (primary too)
        Iliac anchor (mechanism unclear)
        Hydrodynamic drag (magnitude small)
        Tension distal positioning (free-floating)
    Limitations
      N=6 small
      Single center
      Selection bias survivor
      Operator experience
      No catheter shape quantification
    Next Steps
      EMR PACS data 6 cases
      Paper outline
      Phantom validation future
